Bosses are major named encounters that are stronger, tougher, and more
rewarding than normal mobs.

Many bosses are assigned a visible tier:

  T1   T2   T3   T4   T5

In general, higher boss tiers mean:

  more health and staying power
  more dangerous pressure or mechanics
  stronger reward expectations
  a bigger fight that is less suited to casual overlevel farming

Boss kills are often announced on the Events channel. A few bosses may
explicitly opt into mocking much higher-level killers, but normal boss
announcements do not shame players for being overlevel.

Bosses are not all meant for the same stage of progression. Treat the
tier as a clue to the seriousness of the encounter.

